        <headline>Flood Advisory issued July 29 at 9:58PM MDT until July 30 at 1:45AM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Urban and small stream flooding caused by excessive
rainfall is expected.

* WHERE...Portions of central and southwest Montana, including the
following counties, in central Montana, Meagher. In southwest
Montana, Broadwater.

* WHEN...Until 145 AM MDT.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 954 PM MDT, Doppler radar indicated heavy rain due to
thunderstorms. This will cause urban and small stream
flooding. Up to 1 inches of rain has fallen.
- Additional rainfall amounts up to 1 inch are expected over
the area. This additional rain will result in minor flooding.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
White Sulphur Springs and Ringling.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.

Be especially cautious at night when it is harder to recognize the
dangers of flooding.</instruction>
